  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support for Agroecological Production and Alternatives to Coexist with the Semi-Arid Ecosystem in Chapada do Apodi-RN</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The western region of Rio Grande do Norte has a lack of public policies that benefit rural communities, which has led to some of the highest instances of social inequality in the country. Conventional farming and ranching models have also strongly influenced small farmers and settlement residents, who face resistance from technicians when they experiment with ways to live in harmony with the semi-arid ecosystem. The project will benefit 355 families and another 600 families by passing on the gift, by providing training in ways to coexist with the environment. Systematization of agroecological production experiences will improve the quality of life for these families, and strengthen proposals for long-term coexistence with their agro-ecosystems. Concern for natural resources, and for present and future generations, while constructing a sustainable development model will also be considered.</narrative>
  </description>
